r trusting this company.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6
To date, consumers have not been able to recover any loss of assets through=
 Voyager=E2=80=99s supposed FDIC insurance.

The  CFTC case, though, is more about the details of Voyager=E2=80=99s oper=
ations; the gist is that Voyager was desperate to gamble away its customers=
=E2=80=99 money, and did:

Voyager transferred large volumes of pooled customer assets to multiple hig=
