<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The regulatory situation in the US is that the=
re are exchange-traded funds that allow people to speculate on Bitcoin (and=
 Ether), but those funds hold Bitcoin (or Ether)=C2=A0<em>futures</em>, not=
 actual Bitcoins. The US Securities and Exchange Commission has, so far, de=
clined to approve spot Bitcoin ETFs (funds that just hold Bitcoins). It has=
 said that this is because the spot Bitcoin market is largely unregulated a=
nd so there is a risk of manipulation, whereas Bitcoin futures trade on reg=
ulated US exchanges and so are safer. This has always <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33044024.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMDcvZnR4LXdhbnRzLWl0cy1iaXRjb2=
lucy1iYWNrLWZyb20tZ3JheXNjYWxlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTYyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZ=
WRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTAxNiZ1dG1fY2Ft=
cGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBaebddd51" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  struck =
me</a> as incoherent (manipulating the spot market also manipulates the fut=
ures), and in August <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/33044024.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVz=
LzIwMjMtMDgtMjkvZ3JheXNjYWxlLWNhbi1iZS1hLWJpdGNvaW4tZXRmP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTY=
yM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV=
90ZXJtPTIzMTAxNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd=
05bcc32" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  a federal appeals court ruled</a> that it was =E2=80=9Ca=
rbitrary and capricious,=E2=80=9D which <em>probably=C2=A0</em>means that t=
he SEC will have to approve spot Bitcoin ETFs pretty soon.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But it hasn=E2=80=99t yet! Bloomberg=E2=80=99s=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33044024.256428/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMTYvYml0Y29p=
bi1zdXJnZXMtYWJvdmUtMzAtMDAwLW9uLWV0Zi1hcHByb3ZhbC1zcGVjdWxhdGlvbj9jbXBpZD1=
CQkQxMDE2MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldH=
RlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEwMTYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB0bd333b7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">  Vildana Hajric reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bitcoin reversed an earlier gain of as much as=
 10% after BlackRock said that its application for an exchange-traded fund =
that invests directly in the cryptocurrency is still under review.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe iShares Spot Bitcoin ETF applicat=
ion is still under review by the SEC,=E2=80=9D a spokesperson said. Bitcoin=
 was up about 3% to $28,000 as of 10:12 a.m. in New York on Monday after br=
iefly jumping to $30,000.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Speculation swirled on social media that Black=
Rock, which in June submitted an application for a spot-Bitcoin ETF, receiv=
ed a green-light from the US Securities and Exchange Commission to launch t=
he first such product in the US. That spurred the surge in the largest coin=
, though Bitcoin quickly reversed the majority of those gains after the rum=
or was debunked.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, the episode suggests that there remains=
 a lot of excitement and hope for a spot-Bitcoin product in the US, which r=
egulators have in the past refused to allow. They=E2=80=99ve previously cit=
ed market manipulation, among other reasons, for not granting an endorsemen=
t. However, the incident also serves as a reminder that Bitcoin=E2=80=99s p=
rice can easily be moved by gossip or hearsay.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, I am not=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>sympat=
hetic to the SEC=E2=80=99s objections to a spot Bitcoin ETF. But this story=
 makes me a little more sympathetic? The price of Bitcoin jumped by 10% bec=
ause people on social media were saying, falsely, that BlackRock=E2=80=99s =
spot Bitcoin ETF was approved. Seems like the sort of thing that could be m=
anipulated!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously the Chicago Mercantile Exchange fron=
t-month Bitcoin futures also briefly jumped above $30,000 today. If you wan=
t to move the price of Bitcoin=C2=A0<em>futures=C2=A0</em>with gossip and h=
earsay,=C2=A0that is pretty much exactly as easy as moving the price of spo=
t Bitcoin with gossip and hearsay, because they are kind of the same price.=
</p>
