<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I used to work at an investment bank and, well=
, I don=E2=80=99t want to say that I witnessed anyone abusing their meal al=
lowance, but let=E2=80=99s=C2=A0say that I can easily imagine how it might =
come about. You finish work early but stay at the office an extra 15 minute=
s just to be able to claim your <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/33044024.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly9ueXBvc3QuY29tLzIwMjIvMDQvMTkvZ29sZ=
G1hbi1zYWNocy1yYWlzZXMtZGFpbHktZGlubmVyLWFsbG93YW5jZS1ieS01LWFmdGVyLWNvbXBs=
YWludHMv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB268f6e4c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> $30</a> dinner allowan=
ce. Or you order your dinner and take it home to eat, rather than being cha=
ined to your desk as the meal allowance assumes. You order two cheap items,=
 eat one, and bring one home for your partner, or for lunch tomorrow. You o=
rder dinner for a group of analysts on your desk, it comes to more than $30=
 per person, and you throw in the names of a few analysts who aren=E2=80=99=
t there so you can use their allowance too. Or you do one of the seven more=
 creative minor abuses that my readers are going to email me about today.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, I am not <em>saying </em>that I witness=
ed any of this behavior, necessarily, in so many words. But I can imagine i=
t. I can even imagine that the bank wouldn=E2=80=99t mind it that much. The=
 numbers involved are small, relative to bankers=E2=80=99 pay and to the va=
lue of keeping them at work late; an analyst=C2=A0<em>scheming to stay late=
r at work=C2=A0</em>is probably good for the bank. Also a certain risk appe=
tite and ethical flexibility probably=C2=A0help too. It=E2=80=99s probably =
not even worth it for the bank to audit any meal receipts. If it=E2=80=99s =
under the allowance, just pay it, who cares.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, if a bank=C2=A0<em>does=C2=
=A0</em>aggressively audit meal expenses, it might find, let=E2=80=99s say,=
 many many many cases of mild meal-allowance abuse. And then it can send ev=
ery involved analyst an email saying =E2=80=9Chey it looks like you ordered=
 two entrees with your allowance, we=E2=80=99re gonna deduct $11.95 from yo=
ur paycheck, don=E2=80=99t do it again.=E2=80=9D And then the bank would sa=
ve $11.95 per analyst.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Which is not worth it. But it would also get a=
=C2=A0<em>few=C2=A0</em>analysts who write back indignantly with elaborate =
fictional stories about the chain of events that led to them ordering two e=
ntrees with their meal allowances. And then it could investigate those stor=
ies, and if they turn out to be false, it could=C2=A0fire those analysts, w=
hich is=C2=A0good, because=C2=A0they=C2=A0are a real compliance risk.=C2=A0=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/33044024.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlb=
nQvYTc5MzQxMTEtZmQ1Ny00YmJkLWJkMzktNmMyOTUyMzYxNzVk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB4ada4eea" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;"> this guy</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Citibank has won an employment lawsuit against=
 a banker who was dismissed for submitting an expenses claim that included =
coffee and sandwiches for his partner and lying about it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Szabolcs Fekete, a senior analyst, sued the ba=
nk alleging unfair and wrongful dismissal after he was ousted over the expe=
nses he submitted after a three-day work trip to Amsterdam in 2022. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fekete, who had worked at Citi since 2015, tra=
velled with his partner, who was not a bank employee, on his trip to Amster=
dam the tribunal noted. He submitted his expenses claim in late July and cl=
aimed that the amounts were well within the bank=E2=80=99s =E2=82=AC100 a d=
ay limit. However, a senior manager informed him that his expenses claim wo=
uld be rejected because he believed the meals on the receipt had been for t=
wo people.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the ruling, which was made public=
 on Friday, Fekete replied by email that: =E2=80=9CI was on the business tr=
ip by myself and that I had 2 coffees as they were very small.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The senior manager questioned his answer, sayi=
ng: =E2=80=9CThe receipt appears to have two sandwiches, two coffees, and a=
nother drink=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89Are you advising that th=
is was all consumed by you?=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fekete replied: =E2=80=9CYes that is correct=
=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89On that day I skipped breakfast and =
only had 1 coffee in the morning. For lunch I had 1 sandwich with a drink a=
nd 1 coffee in the restaurant and took another coffee back to the office wi=
th me and had the second sandwich in the afternoon=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=
=80=89.=E2=80=89Which also served as my dinner.=E2=80=9D ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The ruling noted that after further queries fr=
om the manager, Fekete replied: =E2=80=9CAll my expenses are within the =E2=
=82=AC100 daily allowance. Could you please outline what your concern is as=
 I don=E2=80=99t think I have to justify my eating habits to this extent.=
=E2=80=9D ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Later in August, Fekete confirmed that some of=
 the food had been consumed by his partner and Citi=E2=80=99s investigation=
 in October concluded that he had breached the company=E2=80=99s expense ma=
nagement policy and had lied during an internal investigation. =E2=80=A6</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The judge said in the ruling: =E2=80=A6 =E2=80=
=9CI am satisfied that even if the expense claim had been filed under a mis=
understanding, there was an obligation upon the claimant to own up and rect=
ify the position at the first opportunity. I accept that the respondent req=
uires a commitment to honesty from its employees.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Should a senior manager have spent time haggli=
ng over a=C2=A0=E2=82=AC100 meal bill? Not as such, no. Should a senior man=
ager have spent time investigating and firing a guy who invented elaborate =
lies to tell his boss in order to cover up an unjustified free sandwich? Ye=
s? That=E2=80=99s bad? Being aggressive with expense reports, meh, whatever=
,=C2=A0maybe on balance a=C2=A0<em>good=C2=A0</em>trait in an investment ba=
nker. But writing tons of easily checkable lies in email and being indignan=
t about it just seems like a bad compliance risk.</p>
